>the games are not picked up, at what point do they fall into the public
>domain?

Copyright ends 50 years after the death of the author.  For corporate
copyright, the figure is 50 years plus X after publication.  (I think X=30,
but I\'m not certain offhand.)

So don\'t hold your breath.  (And also keep in mind that widespread copyright
violation will make acquisition by another company more unlikely.)

On the bright side, Runequest has survived a similar interregnum, so it can
be done.
