I\'ll grant you that.

>The needed tubes to implement the gates are TL0 because glass and
>copper wire are TL0.

Metalworking is TL 1, isn\'t it? And I did suggest that there might well be
a difference between early metalworking and fine metalworking - possibly
more than one. And there\'s a difference between making glass drinking
vessels and vaccum tubes.

>Vaccum is probably also TL0.

What makes you say that? Could you create a vacuum using only TL 0 tools?

>Electricity is TL0 because lightnings are older than humankind.

Ho ho.

>Punch cards to supply input are easy, a
>punch card writer (for output) shouldn\'t be that complicated. An extern
>clock to operate the ALU built from tube-gates could be supplied manually.
>So with some endurance and some help it should be possible? :-)

A very crude, low-capacity calculator might be possible. In fact, it is.
It\'s called an abacus (and not so crude, either).



