> stuff meant for players.
[and other stuff snipped]

Other people have pointed you at the droyne and Secret of the Ancients,
but actually you should pay more attention to that "cryptic stuff".
EVEN AMONG EXPERTS (like your archeologist player) the Ancients
are still mostly a mystery. The Ancients have been a subject of study
for the last ten thousand years, and most questions are STILL best
anwered by "We don\'t know."


What _is_known?

They lived a quarter-million years ago, and were the most technologically
advanced race in existence, past or present. They ranged all over
Charted Space, and spread humaniti across the stars. They vanished
200,000 years ago in what is assumed to be a cataclysmic war, judging
from some of the wreckage (which includes asteroid belts that
_used_ to be planets).
     Their technology is estimated to have been TL 25-35, though it\'s
tough to rate anything that advanced. Complicating things further,
nearly every Ancients site seems to stem from its own
technological base -- standards, architecure, materials, all are
unique to each site, causing some to question whether the Ancients
were actually a single race. Remarkably, a rare few artifacts have
been found that were still functional, after millenia of neglect. Most,
however, are inert and have no discernable purpose.

The identity of the Ancients is unknown, but three modern major
races have _some_ sort of tie to them:

Humaniti: Terra is the only world with a fossil record of humans
and proto-humans prior to the Ancients period. Apparently the
Ancients removed some humans from Terra, and those humans
became the Vilani, Zhodani, and various human Minor Races.
Some minor races show indications of genetic manipulation.

Vargr: Terran canines genetically uplifted to sapience and
bipedalism. There are no known "Vargr minor races", so
it seems the Vargr were only placed (or survived) on Lair.

Droyne: Much has been made of the link between the Ancients
and the Droyne, but to put it in perspective, most of what is
known about the Droyne vis-a-vis the Ancients could just as
equally describe humans or vargr.
     The Droyne homeworld has never been identified. The Droyne
were spread onto many worlds, just as humans were. Many other
worlds have Chirpers, a degenerate, uncasted form of Droyne.
(Some researchers think using the term "degenerate Droyne" for Chirpers
gets things backwards. These scientists believe that the Droyne are
uplifted Chirpers, something well within Ancient capabilities, as it is a less
radical alteration than the vargr were.)

*******************************

Overall, your archeologist player will probably know the details
about assorted "cryptic player stuff" better than anyone else
and have a firmer grip on the breadth of general information,
but is no more likely to know the "real details" of the Ancients
than a merc, free trader, or plumber. The information just isn\'t there.
Ancientology is long on speculation and mysterious artifacts,
but maddeningly short on hard, verifiable facts.


John Bogan
