>   No! Don\'t hang up. Hear me out :-)
>   They are enough alike that it wouldn\'t require
> that much overhead to do them all. Look at The
> Traveller Chronicle, for example.
>   Since Marc is suggesting having up to twelve
> different "time streams" of support (somthing
> I highly approve of) you could even stratiate
> them along those lines.
>   For example for the Virus age, use the TNE
> rules as the base rules for the majority of
> the supplements for those lines. For the
> Rebellion age, use MegaTraveller. For Classic
> Imperium, use Classic Traveller.
>   I imagine the majority of people primarily
> interested in each of those settings is
> also primarily interested in those rule-sets.
>   Makes sense to me. How about you?
>
>               Jo
>
> ----

I think it makes more sense to construct a rules-set with the following
ideas:
- Independence from any one universe.
- Backward compatibility with old rules.
- Detailed rules for things like Cyberpunk and Cloning.


Some examples of what I am talking about ...
Psionics are a rather rare thing in Traveller because the rules for
testing and acquisition of psionics are based on Imperial and planetary
local law.


Tech Levels
The highest tech level that any world can obtain without Imperial influence
is 8. By Imperial influence I mean a Starport or a military base. This
makes it impossible for worlds with even a low jump capability from
developing. However they have at least in the Imperial Universe
since we all of these aliens. I suggest that instead that there be some
kind of sentient population test roll.

Backward compatibility should exist because there\'s lots of good stuff in
Traveller. I have not read any of the stuff from TNE but if their character
generation system does not have a survival rule then that is an improvement.

Alot of the stuff put out by DGP is very good, such as their detailed world
manager. I have a feeling they could update those for a new set of rules
if they needed to.

As for cyberpunk. Cyberpunk has become part of Science Fiction genre now,it
wasn\'t when Traveller first came out. I think its time to add rules for
its mechanics and some chip building rules. Please don\'t add more
stuff about Imperial Law and uses of it.


Matthew S. Harelickhttp://hertz.njit.edu/~msh9848


