    'month' => '01',
    'topic' => 'World Populations',
    'body' => 'Much of this discussion about tech levels overlooks something of extreme
importance. Most of the populations of these worlds are not indigenous to
the worlds they are on. This is evident simply because they all generally
humans of the same evolutionary stage. Coincidence, I think not. The
populations of most worlds are simply colonists or decedents of colonists.
This being the case, discussion of initial technologies and primitive
technological developments is not relevent.
As I have said before, TL is a measure of availability. It is ridiculous to
think of a group of colonists placed on a world having to rediscover fire
and re-invent the wheel.

Simon Harding










