>
>I\'m considering (only CONSIDERING, Dave! Don\'t panic!) switching my RC campaign
>over to the MegaTraveller system to ease the transition to the next version of
>TRAVELLER, which I fully expect to be more like MT than TNE. I\'m not very
>experienced with MT\'s ship design rules, however, and would therefore like to
>know; can you build some of the newer ships (the AURORA Clipper or the VICTRIX
>class) with MT? or at least come reasonably close? Any other suggestions on how
>to recreate the RC background using MT are also appreciated. As I said, this is
>just an experiment at this stage. Thanks!

You\'ll need to get hold of the following Books: Hard Times and 3g^3. Hard
times is a GDW MT that gives the decrepitness prior to the virus (and most
of the collapse), pregravitic and multi-stage/sectional hull rules. 3g^3
can be used to convert the Muzzle Energy to MT\'s P/A D format. If you\'re
using aircraft, you\'ll need COACC for those. You might also want to note
that task difficulties in MT and TNE correlate as follows:

MT              TNE
Simple          Easy
Routine         Average
Difficult       Difficult
Formidable      Formidable
Impossible      Impossible

By the by, does someone out there have the MT wet naval design procedures?
I haven\'t been able to lay my hands upon them up here (Anchorage AK).


-Wil

