    'index' => 'ac379',
    'month' => '01',
    'body' => 'In xboat 502, Susan Marie Shock <34ZBTXQ@CMUVM.CSV.CMICH.EDU> asks:

>I\'m not very
>experienced with MT\'s ship design rules, however, and would therefore like to
>know; can you build some of the newer ships (the AURORA Clipper or the VICTRIX
>class) with MT? or at least come reasonably close?

Ha ha. I shouldn\'t think so, given the amount of inconsistency going the
other way, i.e. from MT to FF&S. The MT ship design rules, though flawed
(even after you\'ve got the errata for them), a little less flexible than
FF&S and thus there is going to be less possibility of variation between
converted designs - I\'m thinking particularly of things like hull armour
which is quite complex in FF&S but in MT requires only a % of the total
ship\'s volume (if I remember correctly).

Re changing your game\'s rules back to MT from TNE, I\'d be wary at the
moment, since it is a long way from Marc saying "I\'d like to..." or "I\'m
thinking of..." to actually seeing said rules in a printed rule book.

I would hope that whatever the revamped Traveller rules look like, they
won\'t _prevent_ you from continuing to play with one of the original
CT/MT/TNE systems if you prefer that.

Andy Lilly
Coordinating BITS (British Isles Traveller Support)

