    'body' => '>It has been suggested that the Gulf War is an example of superior technology
>defeating mass and that this can and should be applied to the Terran victory
>in the Nth Interstellar War. The suggestion is that a sufficient tech
>difference would have been like "magic" to the low tech participants. This
>is likely true, even allowing for the minimal *actual* difference between
>most Traveller TLs.

I don\'t agree.  First of all, there was also a huge difference in the
training and leadership involved (a difference that, in the American
Civil War, allowed Southern forces to acheive victory over armies
that were superior in both numbers and equipment).

Second of all, the advantage that superior technology gives you
is greatly diminished when you go from defeating forces to
occupying and holding territory.  In the Gulf War things would
have been a lot different if we had needed to hold territory with
a significant population.

