  {
    'body' => 'You asked for it, you got it... in no particular order

1-10(give or take?). ALIEN SOURCEBOOKS

These could be presented as one per alien, in a huge compendium, or
something in between (a la the DGP alien books).  The important thing is to
get detailled sourcebooks out for aliens in the game ASAP.  In fact, I\'d
like to see rules in the basic game for generating some of the more common
aliens of the Imperium (e.g. Vargr and Aslan), so players can start playing
them right away.

Besides the major races, it would be really good to have access to all the
minor races that have popped up over the years.  Unless somebody has been
hoarding all TRAVELLER msterial ever published, they have no real idea of
what a Virushi or an Ael Yael is, and even if they do, they have no idea how
to properly generate (or play) a Vegan or "Dandie" (I refuse to spell the
real name out) PC or even NPC.

Also, somewhere in there, it would be good to have general guidelines
somewhere for referees who want to design their own aliens or adapt them
from other sources.  The universe is a big place, and it\'s teeming with life.


11.  I.I.S.S. FIELD GUIDE

This would:

a) Describe the history and operation of the Scout service in detail.  This
would be nice, but not necessary.  If, as people are saying, there will be a
number of possible time periods, it would be useful to detail how what the
Scouts do in the early days of the Imperium was different from what they did
circa The Rebellion/The Short Dusk/Hard Times/Whatever.  This would also be
a good section to suggest potential adventures for scout characters.

b) Give rules for coping with planetary wildernesses--extremes of heat and
cold, foraging, moving across rugged terrain or unusual environments
(mountain, water, etc.)  As with the aliens, this covers a lot of
information that people who aren\'t avid collectors just don\'t have.

c) Give rules for wilderness operations for starships.  This would go beyond
refuelling at the local gas giant and deal with things like how you ut down
a starship when you\'re landing on a flat patch of ground rather than a class
A starport.  Also, when you take your scout/courier on long surveys, just
how much space does a week of supplies take up?


12.  WORLD DETAILLING

Although many have brought up that the basic TRAVELLER world generation
system isn\'t very "logical", it\'s quick and easy and, quite frankly, I want
to change as few things as possible with the new system.  With this said,
some way of adding onto that is necessary--if for no other reason, than to
help referees figure out how long the local day is or what the temperature
is.  I\'m not sure if this should be like _Scouts_, _World Builder\'s
Handbook_, or something entirely different.  One nice addition, from 2300AD
would be some way of estimating what kind of major facilities (e.g.
university, trans-grav rail, etc.) are on the planet.


13.  DESIGN SOURCEBOOOK

When I switched to MT, I appreciated the fact that I could design vehicles
from the ground up.  Although I never played TNE and have heard mixed (at
best) reviews of FFS, I like the idea of being able to design *anything*
from the ground up.  I agree with what others have said, though, in that it
should be simple enough to do without a computer and that it would be good
to have a simple way of expressing an item\'s capabilities.  (Another
UPP?--"Universal Product Profile")


14.  ROBOTS and CYBORGS and ANDROIDS (Oh, my!)

Although some of these could be included in the above sourcebook, it might
be better to have something separate to keep all the "created beings" in one
place.  Just as I\'d like to see some alien examples in the basic game, so
would I like to see 1 or 2 robots in the equipment list.  It would be a
useful reminder that this *is* SF, after all.


15.  JTAS RIDES AGAIN!

Not that this journal per se needs to be resurrected, but there should be
some *regular* journal devoted exclusively to TRAVELLER.

16.  BELLS and WHISTLES

I like the idea of t-shirts, etc.  Also, things like the ID cards in
Supplement 12 were really neat.  If there is a journal, then there could
perhaps be a pge devoted to this sort of thing in each issue.



Thank you for listening.  I also have ideas on what I\'d like to see in the
basic game, but will save that for another time.


