1.  I think that the point that is being made is that overwhelming
quantitive superiority will defeat technological superiority, and with a
terrible cost.  Take the Eastern front during WWII.  The Wehrmacht was a
technologically superior superior and much better trained force than the Red
Army.  The Red Army, however, was HUGE.  It is estimated that the Germans
killed some 20 million Soviets.  Losses like that would have bled most
countries white.  The Soviets just absorbed the losses and keep on fighting.

