the ziru Sirka, but what do you mean by "Vilani divisiveness"?  I have
always had the impression that the Vilani were the least divisive, most
co-operative Human race there was.  They make the mythical "Japan, Inc."
look like a Vargr frat party!  If you mean that non-Vilani would have been
happy to see anybody esle in charge, and would serve as a "fifth column", I
could buy *that*, but say it if that\'s what you mean.

While I\'m on the subject, why have all the historians of the future ignored
