>on the Xboat network is as a fast network of communications for the
>Imperium.  Jump Torpedoes are not only 50% fastet, the can be
>sent to or from _any_ world.

You seem to assume that j-torps are capable of jump-6. I\'ve
always had the impression that j-5 and j-6 drives were restricted to the
military. I can\'t remember where I got that impression (Traveller
Adventure, maybe.)

>Once you start thinking the consequences of jump torpedoes through,
>the fact is they make a fundamental difference.  One, that I already
>mentioned, is that, prior to the assisnation of Stephon, various
>powers had been maintaining secret networks of jump-6 capable
>ships.  They got a several week to month jump on the news of
>the assasination.  With jump torpedos, that simply wouldn\'t
>have happened.,

J-torps have been around a long time. People like me have been
thinking about their consequences for a long time. They are entirely
compatable with the CT background.

>Another example, is the fact that, without such communictations,
>a military vessel has to jump into a system blind.  The best they
>can do is send two ships in with one to report back "all clear".
>The problem is that those ships are easily picked off by a force
>that the whole battle group could easily defeat.  But if you
>send in the whole battle group you risk a major defeat.

Even without j-torps, the navy has always had this capability.
Problem is, the information you gather is two weeks old before the main
fleet arrives. That\'s true with both j-torps and scout ships.

>Date: Mon, 29 Jan 1996 16:41:48 -0800
>From: Summers@Ethyl-the-Frog.ARC.NASA.gov (David P. Summers)

>The fact is that X-boats are presented as the fastest form of
>communications unless you can afford the huge cost of maintaining...

I\'m not aware that GDW ever presented j-torps as being faster than
X-boats.

>If you like jump torps enought that you are willing to make
>a significant change the background, that\'s fine.  But you
>have to be aware that you are making a significant change.

I\'ve never had to make any change at all in the background.
(Well, I had to make one. Before I bought Leviathan, I had told my
players that jump vehicles couldn\'t be under 100 tons. After I bought
Leviathan, I had to tell them, "Oops, I was wrong.") J-torps affect the
X-boat network about as much as automated drones affect Federal Express
today.

>Date: Tue, 30 Jan 1996 10:58:35 -0500 (EST)
>From: Charles Collin <charles@hebb.psych.mcgill.ca>

>To Phil:
>You can have warp drives and phasers in _your_ background for all I care,
>but the debate here is about the Traveller universe.  Granted that jump
>torps are mentioned in Leviathan, but that was put out by DGP and GDW

The CT universe included Leviathan, which was one of the Little
Black Books put out by GDW. When I bought Leviathan, MT was not yet
imagined; I had never even heard of DGP.

>seems to have jumped on their apparent error after publication, stating
>that these torps were Ancients artifacts.  Having jump torps and jump
>gates in the Traveller universe is going to change it fundamentally.  As
>others have mentioned, one of the fundamental aspects of the Traveller
>universe is slow communication speeds.  GDW has specifically mentioned
>this as one of the bases for their background:  The communication
>system is analogous to the 18th century (paraphrased from "The Traveller
>Book").

When did GDW backpedal on j-torps? I never heard of them being
described as ancient artifacts. How would Leviathan get hold of ancient
artifacts? That sounds like a stretch to me. The Imperium would not let
its archeological treasures go out into the wilds of unexplored space
without good reason.

>Your explanation for why the Imperium doesn\'t officially use jump
>gates seems a little thin to me.  You basically said that the Vilani are
>stodgy and don\'t like to change systems very often.  What about other
>nations?  The Darrians, Sword Worlders, and Zhodani (to name a few) all
>use jump ships instead of jump gates.  Why?  And why has their never been
>mention of jump gates anywhere?

I\'m not clear on what jump gates have to do with j-torps. I\'ve
never even heard j-gates MENTIONED in CT. Obviously, they could affect
CT background by quite a bit.

-Rob


P.S. The real reason X-boats have become unfeasable is that the new MT
ship design rules don\'t require the huge jump-fuel consumption that CT
assumed. In MT, it\'s trivial to build a cheap 100-ton ship with manuever
drives and j-4. In CT, it was impossible; X-boats had no manuever. That
poses quite a retcon problem. That\'s one of the reasons I never used MT
ship design.

-Rob

