    'topic' => ' Jump Torps',
    'body' => '>Reply-To: xboat@MPGN.COM
>  8) Jump Torps
>        by Charles Collin <charles@hebb.psych.mcgill.ca>
>
>        All this to say that if jump torps were allowed by eliminating
>the 100 ton rule (i.e., if they were allowed by the physics of the
>Traveller universe), then they would be used extensively and would change
>the Traveller universe in many fundamental ways, not the least of which
>is the marginalization of the X-boat network.  X-boats could still be
>used to carry cargo and such, but it would most likely be much faster
>and more economical to have small unmanned vessels carrying the messages
>if this was possible.

I have always treated the 100-disp.ton limit as a matter of the smallest
*Survivable* jump bubbles, and anything smaller cannot use a hull grid
design, but must use one of the "old" coil based drives. Since few yards
use the old tech (in my useage, it\'s got a +1 to misjump chance under MT,
or a 1 in 6 chance of aggravation under TNE), they cost quite a bit (due to
custom manufacture), mass and displace the same, and cannot generate a
field smaller than that for a 100 dt field, so all small craft with J-Dirve
have coils. J-Torps work just fine, but still need to have the external
fuel source, as they require J fuel ammounts equal to 100 ton ships. And
need to be kicked away before they engage the full field (some 20m).

Notice, I HAVE rationalized the MT drives with CT/RSB descriptions of
J-Drive Tech.


-Wil

