    'body' => 'Some more comments on shooting at a starship in port.

>From: PICL115@FSPHY1.HEP.FSU.EDU

Tom writes:

>My question concerns a conversion between starship damage and some of
>the 10D+ damages that can be achieved from weapons in Book 4: Mercenary.
>Starship damage is done in "hits" (i.e. each laser that hit gets to 
>role once on the "hit location" table of Book 2, missles get 1D6 "hits"
>and High Gaurd has other tables).  Is there any official (or working 
>unofficial) method to determine how many pts of damage (e.g. 16D)
>constitues a "hit" if the weapon is used to fire at a starship.
>If anyone has any workable scheme on this I\'d like to hear it.

I wrote yesterday suggesting the use of Striker rules. (Rule #75 from Book
2) I\'ve since re-read rule 75 and saw that it was pretty simple so I
thought I\'d outline it here:

CT Book-2 starships have a Striker armor factor of 40. To find the hits
on a starship, roll two dice on High Guard\'s hit result table. Add six
to the result. Then add the Striker Armor Factor (40). Then subtract the 
weapon\'s Striker penetration value.

Then look on the HG table; you have your hit!

Here are the penetrations (at effective range) of some of Mercenary\'s
weapons according to the Striker rules (which are now out-of-print): 

