First I would like to thank everyone (especially Robert Flammang and
his "Striker" post who responded to my "starship damage" line.  It
has helped a lot.  If there are any more ideas out there please
keep them coming.

I may be out of place here, but I would like to make a request.
When I signed up on Xboat, I thought it was an extremely good
resource for trying to get a handle on rules that I thought were
vague--by seeing how other people handled them.  I could then
chose the interpretations I liked and disregard the rest.  Each
ref. has his universe:  if its workable, ref and players alike
have a great time,  if its to "hokey" (to use a recent xboat
word) the ref. usually finds himself without any willing players.

I\'m going on about all this due to the recent Mass Driver Masequer,
Tech Wars, and now The Nth J-torp war.  People present their ideas
on Xboat because they work for them and their players; in such
a situation there is no right and wrong.  If a ref. is a no-nonsense
stiff rules-are-law type and it works for him--thats great.  If
some of us bend the rules a bit thats OK too.  (Rebellion--what
rebellion?  Stephron--who\'s he?  These aren\'t in my rules so I don\'t
really mind if J-torps mess this up.  Yes players can use them but
they also open up opportunities for me as ref.  You cant slam me for
using them any more than I can slam you for progressing with newer
rules and sticking tightly by them)

In short, everyone\'s E-mail address comes with their post.  If you
simply MUST argue, do it off xboat.  Once you\'ve worked out a mutual
solution THEN (by all means) let the rest of us know the outcome.
Lets have the atmosphere on Xboat be a little more friendly and
cut down on the number of incredibly long posts with people bickering.

(As a start, if your going to whollop me for sending this post--spare
everyone else and send it to me direct)

On a positive note:  This is an incredible resource, full of good ideas.
Lets keep it going.

Thanks

Tom Trelenberg

(P.S.  I\'ll mention again that if anyone knows where to get Superior Model\'s
Starfleet Wars miniatures (i.e. collector\'s clubs, etc...) please let me
know.  Thanks)

