>government could afford to build 100 T message torpedoes, if they were
>useful, and battleships are big enough to carry them. This would be wasteful,
>though, and what they would be more likely to have are scores of couriers.
>Just how many is something one can discuss.

Aside from the fact you are treating all j-torps as being "lost"
(which I would say is poppycock) the fact is that you are treating
large organizations as having resources to waste.  This isn\'t how
it works.  Needs grow just as fast (sometimes faster) than resources.
In a war the Imperium is going to be short of equiment and (more
imporantly) manpower.  If you think the Imperium is going to have
ships and men just sitting around, or loose them sending them into
uncertain situations, when they don\'t have to just because they are
"big" then you are woefully mistaken.  They have a lot of other used
for these men and ships.

