One of the points that people keep missing is that, the inablity to
easily communicate IS ONE OF THE FUNDAMENTAL UNDERPINNINGS OF THE
TRAVELLER UNIVERSE (it\'s in caps because I feel like I need to
stand on the nearest builing and shout it).  The fact is that
no organization has all the comunications it wants.  Not even
the Imperium (this is why it is forced to use a feudal type
of goverment rather than more direct control).  By making
communications easier you are allow more people to get more
info (both civilian and military) and going to allow more
resources to be freed up for other things.

Again, vast resources and VAST NEEDS FOR RESOURCES.  Yes info
is important and they spend resources to get it.  It is also true
that to make that info easier and free up resourses for other
purposes it a big deal.

>A fleet courier costs MCr 255.55 has a crew of 5 men. The Imperium thinks
>in terms of fighting ships that cost from 70 times more and has nearly
>50 times larger crew (and that\'s for a light cruiser; a _Tigress_ costs
>more than 1400 times as much and has a crew more than 800 times larger.

Right, and jump torps are even cheaper.  Thus, for each 50-70
