Figuring out success for an individual is simply a matter of figuring his
adjusted target.  For example, Jo average, with a +2 DM from his stat (I
use stat/3, so 7/3 rounds to 2) and a +1 skill, attempting an Average
diff task (7+), needs a 4+.

I generally use number targets (e.g. "a 7+ task") instead of name targets
(e.g. "an average diff task"), but if one wanted to use diff levels a la
MT with a stat/3 DM, I would simply raise the target by 1:

simple:     4+
average:    8+
difficult: 12+
formidable:16+
impossible:20+

Comments? Criticisms?

Charles.

