Fifthly, if, as you claim, jump torpedoes increase the number of messages
sent (and I agree with you that it propably does) then the saving will be
far less. If, for example, jump torpedoes encourages admirals to send off
two messages per day, where before they would only send one per week, we\'re
already using _more_ money than with the couriers.

>I call that a big difference.

You\'ve never actually played in a TCS campaign, have you? It\'s the question
of scale again. A 30,000 T LC may seem big to you, but to people who command
fleets that are 200 times bigger it dosen\'t make a lot of difference. It
makes _some_ difference, of course, but not a big one. Not one that _must_
change the Traveller background.


