X::>Sorry Jerry...I must apologize for my recent posts to XBOAT.  They
 ::>were based on two misconceptions of mine:

X::>1)  (understandable)  I thought the XBOAT list was CT and the
 ::> TRAVELLER list was MT and above.

 I wouldn\'t swear to it, but that _may_ have been the original idea
 when the two lists split - I honestly don\'t remember.  On the
 other hand, if we can avoid the flammage that goes with an
 excessive desire to avoid bowel evacuation, and can get past an
 unwillingness to consider information provided by a background
 and rules set that may not be to a particular participant\'s
 individual taste, I\'d have no objection to seeing the lists
 recombined.  I do believe that, mechanics and "undesirable"
 background aside, if we can get back to your second assumption,
 _everyone_ can benefit from ideas from both "camps".  Supreme
 Existence only knows how many ideas I\'ve ripped off from (forgive
 me) DMs who posted said ideas in the hakkenslash D&D newsgroups...

X::>2)  (unforgivable)  I thought the lists were a forum in which different
 ::> refs. could contribute their thoughts to be used (or rejected)
 ::> as desired by the other subscribers.  I misunderstood that
 ::> XBOAT was actually a debate forum which would determine who
 ::> had a CORRECT universe and who had universes which were clearly
 ::> WRONG.

 Pfft!  There is no "right" and "wrong" universe; there\'s only the
 "official" (formerly GDW-supported) universe and the "unofficial"
 referees\' variants.  Of course, some variants are less "Traveller"
 than others, but I take the view that if it\'s recognizably
 related to the "official" universe, it\'s Traveller enough to be
 interesting to me...  That\'s one of the reasons I play a homebrew
 combination of rules and backgrounds from all three sets (most
 notably, character generation from TNE, with some reference to
 tables in CT and MT; task system roughly from MT, with some
 homebrew mods for compatibility with TNE skillsets;  quite often
 in a CT universe, although sometimes in the TNE Regency).  Not to
 mention the "paper" I wrote expanding on the profiling of
 starports, and the creation of the whole RICE concept (both over
 on the TNE list).  I like Resource mode better that Flamethrower
 mode, myself.

 Now, take back those apologies and post your brains for picking.
 I am hopeful that, if people around here see a good example,
 they\'ll follow it.

==========================================================================
Jeff Zeitlin                                      jeff.zeitlin@execnet.com
