I once converted the radial velocities of stars within 20 light-
years of Earth (slightly more than Jump-6) to the Brilliant Lances
scale. While this skews the numbers low because it ignores
transverse motion, I think it gives a good sense of the actual
scale of the problem.

Since this is X-Boat, I\'ll remind/inform folks that the BL scale is
half-hour turns over 30,000 km hexes. 1G of thrust over 1 turn
produces a 1 hex change in vector.

The actual information is on a piece of paper *somewhere*, and I
still have it, but can\'t find it right now, so I\'m going by memory.
Please forgive the lack of detail:

Out of around 100 stars, the fastest moved at a speed of 15
(only one star), the next at around 9 (again, one star).
About 70-80% had a speed less than 4.

>Given that Classic Traveller uses constant-accelleration drives,
