My take is slightly different. I think that jump torpedoes could be
disruptive unless some additional assumptions about their cost and
reliability are made, but that such assumptions as are necessary to
keep them in line are quite plausible.

Secondly, I maintain that the CT/MT rules _as they stand_ alows a type of
jump torpedo that dosen\'t even violate the 100 T jump field restriction.
Basically it consists of a jump drive surrounded my a collapsible frame-
work holding the jump net. The contraption is energized from outside and
uses the same grace period that drop tanks do to get far enough away from
the ship not to interfere with jump field.

I do admit that this makes trouble for the background, since I see no
reason why ships can\'t be energized the same way, but I can\'t come up
with a plausible restriction that will disallow this and still allow
drop tanks.


