    'file' => 'XBOAT96/XBT96555.TXT',
    'subj' => 'Aging',
    'from' => 'jsnead@netcom.com',
    'body' => 'Is anyone else bother by the fact that all the wonders of Imperial
medicine have absolutely no effect on aging unless the character is
taking anagathics.  W/o anagathics characters raised in TL 1 and TL 15
environments have no differences in aging.

Does anyone else modify this?

I\'m about to start a campaign I\'m thinking of using:

Characters raised in Prestellar or earlier environments receive no
modifications.

Characters raised in Early Stellar environments start aging one term
later than normal.

Characters raised in Average Stellar environments also receive a +1 to
all aging rolls (ie they start again 1 term later and receive the +1).

Characters raised in High Stellar environments also receive a +2 to all aging
rolls (1 term later aging and +2).

I also limit characters to 5 or 6 terms, to avoid folks playing
over-experienced geezers.

Comments, other solutions?


-John Snead jsnead@netcom.com


