    'body' => 'At 05:28 PM 3/9/96 -0500, John R. Snead wrote:

>So, has anyone else thought about this, or come up with any interesting
>varieties of humans?
>

I\'ve had everything in my campaigns from midgets and dwarves to 8 foot tall
humans and a lot in between.

In some cases I\'ve had humans that were adapted to their particular
homeworld and in some cases couldn\'t comfortably adapt to other worlds
without encounter suits of some sort. Fer instance, I had a race of humans
that their homeworld was a very high G planet. (3G) These people rarely were
over 4\' 6" but were *wide*. THe were incredibly strong and could lift/carry
lots of weight in a normal or low G environment.  I don\'t remember the
science fiction novel I got that idea from.  If I could I\'d give due credit.

Along the lines of non-human variants I\'ve found room for some of the
fantasy races as well.  Orcs being my favorite to throw into a campaign
setting.  They were good for starting barroom brawls and other chaos... :)

Hobbits took the form of the "Shellizan" who took a great deal of pride in
their ability to carry on commerce and some of them were exceptional chefs
as well.

