    'date' => 'Tue, 12 Mar 1996 09:15:49  0600',
    'body' => 'Mr. McGregor,

 I just want you to know that as long as I have access to a web page I will
still build on the RC setting.  I know there are other people out there who
feel the same way.  If you don\'t like it, sorry, but I enjoy the RC setting.
Will I ignore the New Trav 4 setting?  No, I\'d be foolish to do that.  But I
refuse to limit myself to only one time setting to game in.  If you are
going to give up your CT era and setting, you will lose just as much as TNE
players and ref\'s will lose (probably more).  As I understood the way the
new system has been designed, it will be able to be applied to many time
settings.  There is even a supplement for the year 200, Aslan Border Wars, I
think.  Whatever made you think that TNE and the Virus era were history?
What gives you the idea that Mr. Miller thinks the Virus was bad?  Sure he
said he decided to please himself, but I think he was talking about the
rules system.  Who knows wether he liked the Virus era or the CT era more?
He chose to use a completely new era for his completely new game.  This was
surely a business decision.  After seeing all the petty fighting over which
era was better, TNE or CT or MT, Mr. Miller made IMO a very wise decision to
avoid all three while building a customer base.

I feel sory for you.  You seem to want to limit yourself and everyone else
to a single time in the future history of the Imperium.  That is sad.  This
is a game!!!  There should only be the limits that the Ref places on the
game.  If you want a CT era game, by all means, HAVE a CT era game, but do
not tell me that I can\'t have an RC era game just because you don\'t like the
details of the time period.  If you are right, however, and the TNE era is
gone forever, then the CT era is gone as well.



To everyone else:

I\'m sorry to take up space on the mailing list with this.  When I signed up
for the mailing list, I thought it would be a great place to get ideas for
adventures and campaigns.  I was right, but I was shocked to find the
mudslinging and personal little wars going on over differences of opinions.
This list and the Traveller list should be a place to share your ideas
without fear of being condemned for your opinion.  When something I suggest
doesn\'t fit, I expect that to be pointed out to me, however; when I express
my opinion, it is just that, an opinion.  If you don\'t like my opinion,
state your opinion and we can discuss the differences without condemning
each other personally.  Yes, I believe that people can have an intelligent
discussion about differing opinions without putting each other down.  Enough
rambling and sorry for the space, but I had to get this out. I\'m tired of
getting junk mail where all people do is tell how stupid their opponents
ideas and preferences are.


Paul {tiger}

