>MT material.  I\'ve run into at least three references to a human minor=20
>race known as the Suerrat (Solomani & Aslan, MTJ #3, and the old CT=20
>Library data, book A-M).  They seem to be hairy, short, and come from
>Ilelish 2907.  Does anyone know of any more info published on them.  =
Data=20
>on (A UPP to start with) on Ilelish 2907 would be a good start.

I\'ve only been able to dig up bits and pieces here and there. Let\'s see:

The Imperial Encyclopedia has the following to say in Library Data under =
"Major Race":

"The Suerrat (a human race) are considered minor because their =
achievement of interstellar travel utilized generation ships."

Also, I\'ve looked at the HIWG files available at ftp.engrg.uwo.ca. =
There\'s a document on the Answerin by James Maliszewski, who has the =
following to say about the Suerrat:

"Furthermore, thorough various sources I\'ve that the Suerrat were =
transplanted from Massilia (as stated in earlier literature) to Ilelish, =
apparently because GDW and DGP didn\'t want to have another MHR in the =
same sector as the Geonee."

Other documents on the ftp site states that the Suerrat were mentioned =
in Alien Module 8 (which one was that - Darrians?).

UPPs for all worlds in Ilelish can be found at the above mentioned ftp =
site, but for the convenience of those who doesn\'t have ftp access, here =
is the UPP for 2907 Ilelish:

Ilelish       2907 E674983-A    Hi In              204 Im M0 D

Please note that we are speaking about the world Ilelish itself.

Finally, Traveller News Service in Challenge 43 has this newsbit:

"ILELISH/ARRELI (2707 B877831-8)                    Date: 023-1120
  At the Federation Natural History Conference, held at Gitaaz Center in =
Concarraffi, Dr. Javin Stark presented the findings from his recent =
archaeological digs on Ilelish. The centerpiece of the presentation was =
a fossilized Droyne skull, which he estimated to be about 300,000 years =
old.
  "This finding obviously presents us with far more questions than =
answers regarding the history of the world (Ilelish)," Stark stated. =
"The two main questions are, \'How did Droyne get to Ilelish,\' and \'Why =
did they disappear?\' Considering that the date of this skull fits with =
our estimates of when the Suerrat were presumably transplanted to =
Ilelish by the Ancients, it seems reasonable to assume that a sample of =
Droyne were brought to Ilelish as well.
  "As to why they disappeared - it could be that they were exterminated =
while competing with the proto-Suerrat for resources after the Ancients\' =
Final War. An alternate theory proposes that the Ancients may simply =
have discontinued use of Droyne on this world.
  "Unfortunately, we simply don\'t have enough facts to support any =
theory conclusively at this time. Our hope of understanding this find =
lies in locationg more evidence and scrutinizing our data to make sure =
the answer is not before us and simply hiding in the cracks.""

Hope this helps

Mark Seemann
mark@dk-online.dk
