    'topic' => '"Transplanting Campaigns"',
    'month' => '03',
    'index' => 'ac777',
    'body' => 'I can see the point about not transplanting an ongoing campaign. It doesn\'t
work well, I know, I\'ve tried it repeatedly. HOWEVER, the same TYPES of
campaigns can be run in both Era 0 and Era 1050 and Era 1200 if you set
them in the right places, and ignore RSB.

The bulk of the campaigns I have seen, run, played in, or been told about
have been either CT or MT spinward marches or solomani rim. The largest
group left thereafter is RC, then Regency. All of which are definitely
"frontier". some of the items for 1050-1130 are tailored to that era...
very few are specific to it.

T4\'s multi-era support will provide for an unequalled breadth of setting;
also these areas are frontiers only to the imperials... in era 0, there
will be some emergent pocket empires, some local splinters, and lots of
political intrigues.

By Era 200 (aslan border wars) the setting will have fallen into the
imperial culture trap... an imperial culture will have emerged. And the
imperium will then be truly familiar, if not up to the tech specs of 1000+
YI.

Each era seems to be a major turning point in imperial history.

Including the TNE/RC/RSB setting (Ouch! I actually said that!) with its
fallen imperium, no longer recognizeable.

More depth, timed to release shortly before lucas next installment of Star
Wars (Supposedly Summer 97 according to the trades).

Hopefully it will sell... I know everyone up here is excited!


