and Mark Seeman <mark@dk-online.dk> replied:

>"The Suerrat (a human race) are considered minor because their =
>achievement of interstellar travel utilized generation ships."

I believe a comment was made in Vilani & Vargr that they had a STL-based
empire of 25 or so worlds in Ilelish and Gushemege prior to Vilani contact.

>Other documents on the ftp site states that the Suerrat were mentioned =
>in Alien Module 8 (which one was that - Darrians?).

Yeah, I think there were some comments in Darrians, but I forget what.

>Ilelish       2907 E674983-A    Hi In              204 Im M0 D

Ilelish led the Ilelish Revolt in the 400s, and paid dearly for it (see
Rebellion Sourcebook).  Up to then, they\'d been sector capital.  When the
Imperial Navy finally captured the system, they evacuated and sterilized
the lush equatorial zone of the world as an object lesson.  I suspect
that this was a deep blow to the arboreal Suerrat people.

The interview with Jeremii Boden in MT#3 claims that the Suerrat trade
language used in the Ilelish Cultural Region is called Yaudal; this is
probably a subtle in-joke.  (Say it out loud.  Mess with the vowels.
What does Tarzan do? :)  I\'ll probably regret mentioning this....)

The Suerrat are probably one of the more important minor races in the
Imperium, and are probably more commonly seen than you\'d think, even
though their homeworld isn\'t impressive.

  Steve Bonneville
