  Actually, this is the canon explanation - in Rats & Cats, the firm
GenAssist used genetic engineering and "artificial wombs" tended by
robots and a small human staff that churned out thousands of children a
year.  The kids were educated by tapes feeding the subconcious mind.  The
result was a heavily populated productive colony world in twenty years.

  Apparently most coreward worlds were settled this way.  The people
of these colonies saw themselves as Terrans, since they lacked
defined national roots.

