OK, accepted. However, in *all* the advanced (and most of the non-advanced)
human societies presented in all versions of Traveller, women are treated as
full equals (yes, there are some exceptions, but they are all, AFAIR, backward
societies). In the rules, the assumption has been from the start that any of
the careers is available equally to men and women. Sure, you can argue that
Miller and the rest were influenced by western feminism ... but so what? it
is, after all, *their* future ... and in it, women have full equality taken for
granted.

That\'s one thing. Then there\'s another that you aren\'t considering ... given
the known history of the Terran Federation, it is fairly obvious that it is
going to be western dominated. After all, who will foot the bills for all those
neat spaceships ... Bangladesh? Nope, the US, the EEC, Japan, and the like.
Sure, you can assume that some of the Asian "tiger" economies will play a part
-- however, the trends are there (and seem to be of *very* considerable worry
to their leaders!) that they are wanting more and more what we in the West take
for granted ... democracy, equality etc. It seems a virtual certainty that they
will become more and more like us, at least in these matters ... and those that
don\'t obviously have no impact on the society of the future, and so can be
considered to be failures.

