Phillip McGregor <aspqrz@sydney.DIALix.oz.au> said:

>Then, consider this. What did the other planets (outside of Vland) *eat*? We
>are told that the plants and animals of Vland were largely inedible to the
>Vilani ... surely the chances of any planet having *any* food that is edible
>by humans or human descended/related lifeforms is so close to nil as to be
>pointless considering?! Sure, there are two solutions to this --

Traditionally, the Traveller background has made the assumption that most
life in Charted Space seems to be on the most basic level very similar --
most life uses DNA or close analogues, and basic amino acids.  In addition,
since the wide spread of humaniti is due to Ancient intervention, in most
cases supporting sources of food were presumably also transported.

Heck, if we\'ve already accepted hyperdrive and Ancient astronauts visiting
the Earth, I think I can cope with this, too.

  Steve Bonneville
