  {
    'body' => 'Hi All.

The problem of races finding food on other planets is not as big
as some have made it out to be.  While it is true that the biology of
other worlds is unlikely to make things there easily digestible by any
given race, there are ways around this.  When the ancients transplanted
races to other worlds, they need not have transplanted a bunch of edible
species with them.  Instead, they simply could have created some
intestinal flora/fauna which aided in digestion.  We do a similar (though
simpler) sort of thing today for people with lactose intolerance.  In
fact, the reason _we_ are able to digest things is because of help from
our intestinal symbiotes.  For a different world, you just have to make a
different set of intestinal symbiotes which are capable of breaking down
and building up the local foodstuffs into the required basic components,
which are going to be the same everywhere in the universe.  These
intestinal symbiotes are passed from mother to child (IIRC), so you just
have to "infect" the initial inhabitants with them and off you go.

Charles.

