> terran biosphere.

But, it *doesn\'t* support what you are saying. Either that or we\'re not talking
about the same thing at all? I just don\'t see how you can make the statement!
What I said above was that Panspermia means that all life is related ... there
*are* no "alien biospheres" ... and so the Vilani, with their unique and
atypical biosphere, are exposed to diseases that *are* related to terran ones
as soon as they leave their own planet. And to have ruled a large empire (and
conquered it originally) for 2000 odd years means that they must have developed
ways of dealing with those diseases ... and this *does* mean that they will
have some resistance to terran style diseases, or some ability to provide
*artifical* resistance (antibiotic and antiviral analogues, for a start). In
fact, it implies that the *Terrans* will be at least as vulnerable to the
diseases the Vilani bring with *them*.

Don\'t take this as a personal attack on your professional qualifications. We\'re
