    'topic' => 'black curtain',
    'body' => '"The Phoenix" wants to know what\'s behind the black curtain.

I have no idea of any canon that might exist on the subject.

In the only campaign I had in the virus era (with MT rules, I did not
want to change by vehicle designs) I had assumed that a ship with a
suitable virus strand had landed on Sybmquis (sp?) the TL 17 planet with
TL 8 space techonology. The virus had quickly removed the block preventing
them to  achieve space technology (as the locals appear to be or use lots
of robots [see e.g. Robots]) and had started a galaxy conquering project
solely based on robotic workers, automated factories, robotic crews. The
project has to start slow because the virus run planet has to reinvent
some aspects of space technology.

The location of the planet was roughly inside the black curtain as depicted
in the TNE manual.

This was unveiled by Regency spies (as I was assuming that only idiots
would avoid monitoring closely a TL 17 planet) so that the Regency
can start a "save the civilization" effort (reducing the viking jokers to
a client state in the process [it\'s my universe I can wipe out the ones
I do not like!]). The Regency ultimately wins but not by a big margin
and at that point it reunifies Imperium (or what\'s left of it, about 1205).

Of course part of the Regency effort has to be secret because of the
anti-"Nafta" referendum.

                   Massimo

